The detection efficiency for a particular decay event will depend strongly on the decay mode of that event, i.e., either by $\beta$-delayed protons or only by betas. Indeed the detection efficiency of the DSSSD is very different for protons (close to 1) and for $\beta$ particles (much smaller than 1), see Section \ref{eff}. Therefore for nuclei where the decay mode is only by betas, the integration of the parent contribution and descendents will depend on the rather limited $\beta$ detection efficiency $\epsilon_{\beta}$ of the DSSSD. 

