The $\beta$ detection efficiency of the DSSSD is determined by means of known $\beta\gamma$ emitters, i.e., the $T_z$ = -1 nuclei populated in the dataset focused on $^{58}$Zn. As distinct from the $T_z$ = -2 nuclei under study, $\beta$-delayed proton emission is not present in these $T_z$ = -1 isotopes. Indeed their decay proceeds by either $\beta$-delayed $\gamma$ emission or by $\beta$ decay to the ground state, thus they can be used to estimate the $\beta$ detection efficiency of the DSSSD from:

